Year Over Year Analysis

I dont know if this is valid but I compared the registered referees from mid-2021 to the current list.

In 2021, a total of 1,352 officials registered.

In 2022, so far 976 officials have registered.

510 or 52% have at least partially renewed their registrations.

837 officials have yet to update their registration in 2022.

This year, there are 466 officials who are either new or did not register in 2021.

In analyzing the attrition by gender, it turns out a substantial number of referees are registered without a gender (188). This seems to be some error in data collection since this phenomenon is not reflected in 2022 data.

So this graph is filtered for referees registered with a gender.

Dividing registrations into age groups you can see the biggest drop off in re-registering seems to be referees between 15 and 18 years old.
